.TH "ATOMIC.CONF" "5" "" "atomic\-upgrade" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
atomic.conf \[em] configuration file for atomic\-upgrade
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[I]/etc/atomic.conf\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]atomic.conf\f[R] is the configuration file for
\f[B]atomic\-upgrade\f[R](8), \f[B]atomic\-gc\f[R](8),
\f[B]atomic\-rebuild\-uki\f[R], \f[B]atomic\-guard\f[R], and the pacman
wrapper.
It is read on every invocation.
Changes take effect immediately without restarting any service.
.PP
The file format is \f[I]KEY=VALUE\f[R], one per line.
Comments begin with \f[B]#\f[R].
Inline comments are supported when preceded by a space (e.g.,
\f[B]KEEP_GENERATIONS=3 # keep three\f[R]).
Values may optionally be enclosed in single or double quotes, which are
stripped during parsing.
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] inline comment detection splits on the first
\f[CR]#\f[R] (space + hash) occurrence.
Values containing a literal \f[CR]#\f[R] sequence will be truncated at
that point.
This does not affect typical paths or kernel parameters.
.PP
Only allowed keys are accepted.
Unknown keys produce a warning on stderr and are ignored.
The file must be owned by root (uid 0) when at
\f[CR]/etc/atomic.conf\f[R]; otherwise it is rejected entirely.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]BTRFS_MOUNT\f[R]
Mount point for the Btrfs top\-level subvolume (subvolid=5) during
operations.
Default: \f[I]/run/atomic/temp_root\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]NEW_ROOT\f[R]
Mount point for the new snapshot during chroot.
Must differ from \f[B]BTRFS_MOUNT\f[R].
Default: \f[I]/run/atomic/newroot\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]ESP\f[R]
EFI System Partition mount point.
Automatically mounted if not already mounted.
Default: \f[I]/efi\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]KEEP_GENERATIONS\f[R]
Number of non\-current generations to keep during garbage collection.
Must be an integer >= 1.
Default: \f[B]3\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]MAPPER_NAME\f[R]
dm\-crypt mapper name used as a fallback when auto\-detection of the
root block device fails.
Default: \f[B]root_crypt\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]KERNEL_PKG\f[R]
Name of the kernel package.
Determines which \f[I]vmlinuz\f[R] and \f[I]initramfs\f[R] files are
used for UKI builds.
Common values: \f[B]linux\f[R], \f[B]linux\-lts\f[R],
\f[B]linux\-zen\f[R].
Default: \f[B]linux\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]KERNEL_PARAMS\f[R]
Kernel command line parameters appended after the auto\-detected root
device arguments.
Default: \f[B]rw slab_nomerge init_on_alloc=1 page_alloc.shuffle=1
pti=on vsyscall=none randomize_kstack_offset=on debugfs=off\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]CHROOT_COMMAND\f[R]
Default command to run in the snapshot chroot, overriding the built\-in
default of \f[B]pacman \-Syu\f[R].
Command\-line \f[B]\[en] CHROOT_COMMAND\&...\f[R] takes priority over
this setting.
Arguments with spaces are supported via proper shell\-style quote
handling.
Default: \f[I]/usr/bin/pacman \-Syu\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]SBCTL_SIGN\f[R]
Enable UKI signing with \f[B]sbctl\f[R](8) for Secure Boot.
Set to \f[B]1\f[R] to enable, \f[B]0\f[R] to disable.
When disabled, UKI files are built unsigned.
Default: \f[B]0\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]UPGRADE_GUARD\f[R]
Enable the upgrade guard (pacman hook and wrapper).
Set to \f[B]1\f[R] to block direct \f[B]pacman \-Syu\f[R], \f[B]0\f[R]
to allow it.
Default: \f[B]1\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]HOME_COPY_FILES\f[R]
Space\-separated list of files to copy from \f[I]/home//\f[R] into
isolated home subvolumes created with \f[B]\-\-separate\-home\f[R].
Paths are relative to the user\[cq]s home directory.
The \f[B]\-\-copy\-files\f[R] flag on the command line overrides this
value per invocation.
Paths with spaces are not supported.
Default: \f[I](empty)\f[R].
.SH SECURITY
The configuration file must be owned by root when at
\f[CR]/etc/atomic.conf\f[R].
If the file is owned by another user, it is rejected and no values are
loaded.
.PP
Only the keys listed above are accepted.
Attempts to set arbitrary shell variables (e.g., \f[B]PATH\f[R],
\f[B]LD_PRELOAD\f[R]) via the config file are silently ignored.
The file is parsed line\-by\-line with a safe parser \[em] it is never
sourced or evaluated as shell code.
.SH EXAMPLES
Minimal configuration (all defaults):
.IP
.EX
# /etc/atomic.conf
# Empty \[em] all defaults apply
.EE
.PP
Custom ESP and kernel:
.IP
.EX
ESP=/boot/efi
KERNEL_PKG=linux\-zen
.EE
.PP
Enable Secure Boot signing:
.IP
.EX
SBCTL_SIGN=1
.EE
.PP
LUKS with TPM2 auto\-unlock:
.IP
.EX
KERNEL_PARAMS=rd.luks.options=tpm2\-device=auto rw slab_nomerge init_on_alloc=1 page_alloc.shuffle=1 pti=on vsyscall=none randomize_kstack_offset=on debugfs=off
.EE
.PP
Disable upgrade guard:
.IP
.EX
UPGRADE_GUARD=0
.EE
.PP
Keep more generations:
.IP
.EX
KEEP_GENERATIONS=5
.EE
.PP
Default files for isolated homes:
.IP
.EX
HOME_COPY_FILES=\[dq].bashrc .bash_profile .ssh .gnupg .gitconfig\[dq]
.EE
